mplications of this new development for the methodology of religious studies? Leading practitioners of psychological, theological, sociological, anthropological, phenomenological, historical, and hermeneutic approaches examine the mutually enriching interface between religious studies and women's studies, as they explore the broader issue of the interaction between method and the nature of the subject itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aReligionxStudy and teaching. 0aWomen's studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh1 aFiorenza, Elisabeth SchÜssler, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGross, Rita M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Constance A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJonte-Pace, Diane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKinsley, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuether, Rosemary Radford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharma, Arvind, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharma, Arvind, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStenger, Mary Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Katherine K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791488713423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791488713/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles